D, A, Em, G


- Bridge Chord Progression -
Bm, G (x3)
Em, G (x1)

snippet.textDisplay: Have had this song in my car on repeat a few times. I really do love it. I love that she is spreading her message, through song. And its a great message. To the point where i feel like crying when i hear the kids sing. You can feel its power. It sounds like how the feeling of hope would sound like. Its a short song but the message is very clear. and i love the layering of her vocals.. like at 1:04 "oh how quickly they forget" she goes super low with her voice but an octave higher at the same time. What a great vocal layer. Blended so perfect. I love how the song doesn't just finish, it keeps going. Like "if you didnt hear my message during the song, ill make it clearer for you". And all the vocals, the chorus, everything coming together was beautiful. Simple but important song. I hope people are playing this in their cars, on a walk, at the gym, on their headphones, at home. It motivates you to want to change the world. X
